place.name: BARRY
place.gazetteerText: Barry, coast par. and vil. with ry. sta., near Carnoustie, S. Forfarshire, and 8½ miles NE. of Dundee by rail, 5328 ac., pop. 3233; the annual camp of instruction for artillery volunteers in Scotland and the north of England is held here. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)
